# Global Docker ignore rules for the Optimistic Tanuki workspace
# These apply to all builds that use the workspace root as the build context.
#
# Goals:
# - Keep Docker build contexts small and fast
# - Exclude local-only artifacts (coverage, screenshots, logs, etc.)
# - Preserve source and dist outputs needed by Nx/Docker builds

# Node / package managers
node_modules
npm-debug.log*

# Git / IDE / tooling
.git
.gitignore
.github
.vscode
.idea

# Nx / tooling caches and temp
# Keep .nx so Docker builds have access to the Nx project graph
# and cached metadata. Still ignore generic tmp folders.
.tmp
tmp
.temp

# Angular CLI / Vite caches (these confuse Nx project graph inside Docker)
.angular

# Test / coverage / e2e artifacts
coverage
**/coverage

test-results
**/test-results

# E2E and Playwright outputs
apps/*-e2e
apps/**/playwright-report
**/playwright-report
**/playwright-report/**

# Large local-only resources
screenshots
**/screenshots
storage
codepen-material

# Logs
**/*.log

# Dist notes:
# Do NOT ignore dist/ globally; backend Dockerfiles copy dist/apps/<service>
# from the workspace into the image. However, it is safe to ignore any
# hypothetical e2e app bundles under dist/apps/*-e2e, and Storybook output
# (which can contain duplicate Nx project definitions under dist/storybook).
dist/apps/*-e2e
dist/storybook
